# 📄 SonarQube – GitHub Integration Documentation

## 🔷 Overview

This document explains how to integrate SonarQube Server with GitHub using:

* GitHub App (for repository access)
* GitHub OAuth App (for authentication)

This setup enables:

* Importing GitHub repositories
* Running code analysis
* Enforcing Quality Gates
* Breaking pipeline on failure

---

# 🔷 1. Tools Used

* SonarQube Server
* GitHub
* GitHub Actions (CI/CD)

---

# 🔷 2. Architecture Flow

Developer → GitHub → SonarQube → Quality Gate → Pass/Fail

---

# 🔷 3. GitHub App Configuration (Repository Access)

## Step 1: Create GitHub App

Go to:
https://github.com/settings/apps

Click:
New GitHub App

### Fill Details:

* App Name: sonarqube-integration
* Homepage URL: http://<SONARQUBE-IP>:9000

### Webhook:

* URL: http://<SONARQUBE-IP>:9000/api/alm_settings/webhook
* Secret: sonar123

### Permissions:

Repository Permissions:

* Contents → Read
* Pull Requests → Read & Write
* Checks → Read & Write
* Metadata → Read

Click Create App

---

## Step 2: Generate Credentials

From GitHub App dashboard:

* App ID → Copy
* Client ID → Copy
* Client Secret → Generate and copy
* Private Key → Generate (.pem file) and copy full content
* Webhook Secret → same as given (sonar123)

---

## Step 3: Install GitHub App

Click:
Install App → Select Account → Install

---

# 🔷 4. SonarQube GitHub App Integration

Go to:

Administration → Configuration → DevOps Platform Integrations

Click:
Create Configuration → GitHub

### Fill:

* Configuration Name: github-config
* GitHub API URL: https://api.github.com
* GitHub App ID: (from GitHub)
* Client ID: (from GitHub)
* Client Secret: (from GitHub)
* Private Key: (paste .pem content)
* Webhook Secret: sonar123

Click Save

---

# 🔷 5. GitHub OAuth App Configuration (Authentication)

## Step 1: Create OAuth App

Go to:
https://github.com/settings/developers

Click:
OAuth Apps → New OAuth App

### Fill:

* Application Name: sonarqube-oauth
* Homepage URL: http://<SONARQUBE-IP>:9000
* Authorization Callback URL:
  http://<SONARQUBE-IP>:9000/oauth2/callback/github

Click Register Application

---

## Step 2: Generate Credentials

* Client ID → Copy
* Client Secret → Generate and copy

---

# 🔷 6. Configure OAuth in SonarQube

Go to:

Administration → General Settings → Authentication → GitHub

Click:
Create Configuration

Paste:

* Client ID
* Client Secret

Click Save

---

# 🔷 7. Common Errors & Fixes

## Error 1: redirect_uri mismatch

Cause:
Incorrect callback URL

Fix:
Ensure:
http://<SONARQUBE-IP>:9000/oauth2/callback/github

